To create a Symfony repository for the `account` index, you would need to first configure the Elasticsearch bundle in your Symfony project. Once the bundle is installed and configured, you can create a repository class that uses the Elasticsearch client to interact with the `account` index. Here's an example of what the repository might look like:


```php
<?php

namespace App\Repository;

use Elasticsearch\Client;
use Elasticsearch\Common\Exceptions\Missing404Exception;

class AccountRepository
{
 private $elasticsearchClient;
 private $indexName;

 public function \_\_construct(Client $elasticsearchClient, string $indexName)
 {
 $this->elasticsearchClient = $elasticsearchClient;
 $this->indexName = $indexName;
 }

 public function findByIds(array $ids): array
 {
 $params = [
 'index' => $this->indexName,
 'body' => [
 'query' => [
 'ids' => [
 'values' => $ids,
 ],
 ],
 ],
 ];

 $response = $this->elasticsearchClient->search($params);

 return $response['hits']['hits'];
 }

 public function save(array $data): void
 {
 $params = [
 'index' => $this->indexName,
 'id' => $data['id'],
 'body' => $data,
 ];

 $this->elasticsearchClient->index($params);
 }

 public function saveBulk(array $data): void
 {
 $params = [
 'index' => $this->indexName,
 'body' => [],
 ];

 foreach ($data as $item) {
 $params['body'][] = [
 'index' => [
 '\_id' => $item['id'],
 ],
 ];
 $params['body'][] = $item;
 }

 $this->elasticsearchClient->bulk($params);
 }

 public function deleteById(string $id): void
 {
 try {
 $this->elasticsearchClient->delete([
 'index' => $this->indexName,
 'id' => $id,
 ]);
 } catch (Missing404Exception $e) {
 // Document not found
 }
 }
}
```
In this repository class, we inject the Elasticsearch client and the index name into the constructor. We then define several methods for interacting with the index:

* `findByIds`: This method searches for documents in the index with the specified IDs and returns an array of search hits.
* `save`: This method saves a single document to the index.
* `saveBulk`: This method saves multiple documents to the index in a single bulk request.
* `deleteById`: This method deletes a document from the index by ID.

